    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In weighing the Microsoft case (Business Day, May 2), we should remember that computers and the Windows operating system are used throughout the world. There is no guarantee that Microsoft's breakup would not result in the emergence of competitive operating systems from companies in Europe or Asia.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In weighing the Microsoft case (Business Day, May 2), we should remember that computers and the Windows operating system are used throughout the world. There is no guarantee that Microsoft's breakup would not result in the emergence of competitive operating systems from companies in Europe or Asia.</p>
        <p>If Microsoft were based in France, Germany or Japan, I doubt those countries would even consider breaking it up in order to make the world market an easier place for rival companies from other countries.</p>
        <p>YALE EMMER  Sarasota, Fla., May 2, 2000</p>
      </block>
